    "body": "Yes, that is expected behavior. Since modifier wraps the function like a decorator, the variable x which is pushed into the stack at the beginning of the call to `foo` must remain available until the `_;` returns.\r\n\r\nYou showcase an interesting case though, and I think there is a simple optimization to be made here, which is to pop modifier local variables when the `_` statement is in tail position.",
